description:
What: Implement guild.create, guild.list, guild.get, guild.join, guild.leave JSON-RPC handlers in relay/src/ws.rs. Also remove old GROUP_CREATE/GROUP_LIST/GROUP_ADD/GROUP_LEAVE/GROUP_SEND handlers.

Algorithm:
1. Read /home/mark/PROJECT/Agora/relay/src/ws.rs — find the main dispatch match arm and existing GROUP_* handlers
2. Remove handlers for: GROUP_CREATE, GROUP_ADD, GROUP_LIST, GROUP_LEAVE, GROUP_SEND, GROUP_DELIVER (they are replaced by guild.* and channel.*)
3. Remove corresponding struct definitions from imports (GroupCreateParams, GroupAddParams, etc.) if they were in ws.rs directly
4. Add new handlers in the match arm:

   rpc_methods::GUILD_CREATE => {
     // 1. Parse GuildCreateParams from params
     // 2. Build GuildState with:
     //    context = AGORA_CONTEXT, type_ = "GuildState", schema_version = "1"
     //    name = params.name, description = params.description
     //    owner = session.pub_id.0.clone()
     //    admin_set = vec![]
     //    channels = vec![]
     //    mls_group_id = hex::encode(rand::random::<[u8; 32]>())  // random guild signaling group ID
     //    seq = 0, created_at = Utc::now().to_rfc3339(), prev_state_cid = None, proof = None
     //    id = "agora://pending"  // will be set to CID after signing
     // 3. Sign with identity: sign_guild_state(&mut state, &session.pub_id.0, &session_signing_key)?
     //    PROBLEM: ws.rs does not have access to the signing key after auth — see note below
     // 4. Update state.id = format!("agora://{}", guild_cid)
     // 5. Store in DB: state.inner.store.create_guild(&guild_cid, &owner, &owner, &params.name, &state_json)
     // 6. Add creator to members: state.inner.store.add_guild_member(&guild_cid, &owner)
     // 7. Return GuildCreateResult { guild_cid }
     //
     // NOTE on signing key: The relay does NOT have the client's signing key.
     // Two options:
     //   A) Client sends a pre-signed GuildState document (client handles signing)
     //   B) Relay creates an unsigned GuildState and client signs a hash
     //   C) Relay has its own signing key (relay-created guilds, admin = relay)
     // For Phase 1: Option C — the relay creates GuildState signed with relay's Ed25519 key
     // (relay has its own keypair in AppState). The creator's DID is set as admin.
     // This is a simplification for Phase 1; Phase 2 can support client-signed state.
   }

   rpc_methods::GUILD_LIST => {
     // 1. Get session pub_id
     // 2. guild_cids = state.inner.store.list_guilds_for_member(&pub_id).await?
     // 3. For each guild_cid, fetch state_json, parse name/owner, build GuildInfo
     // 4. Return GuildListResult { guilds }
   }

   rpc_methods::GUILD_GET => {
     // 1. Parse GuildGetParams { guild_cid }
     // 2. state_json = state.inner.store.get_guild(&guild_cid).await? (must exist)
     // 3. Return GuildGetResult { guild_cid, state_json }
   }

   rpc_methods::GUILD_JOIN => {
     // 1. Parse GuildJoinParams { guild_cid }
     // 2. Verify guild exists (get_guild returns Some)
     // 3. Add member: state.inner.store.add_guild_member(&guild_cid, &pub_id).await?
     // 4. Return OkResult { ok: true }
   }

   rpc_methods::GUILD_LEAVE => {
     // 1. Parse GuildLeaveParams { guild_cid }
     // 2. Remove member: state.inner.store.remove_guild_member(&guild_cid, &pub_id).await?
     // 3. Return OkResult { ok: true }
   }

5. Add AppState relay signing key:
   In state.rs Inner struct, add: relay_signing_key: ed25519_dalek::SigningKey
   In AppState::new(), generate: let relay_signing_key = ed25519_dalek::SigningKey::generate(&mut OsRng);
   In ws.rs guild.create handler, use: state.inner.relay_signing_key.sign(...)
   Relay DID: make_did_key(&state.inner.relay_signing_key.verifying_key().as_bytes())

Defensive rules:
- All params deserialized via serde_json::from_value — return INVALID_PARAMS error if Err
- Guild existence check before join (return error if not found)
- Owner check not needed for Phase 1 guild.create (caller becomes owner)
- No user input string-interpolated into SQL

Run: cargo check -p agora-relay 2>&1
Report: pass/fail, list all new handler method names added, list all GROUP_* handlers removed.
